Hi Richard

I would try a solution like this (I am just typing it into this form
and haven't tested this code, so there might be some errors. Here I
also write the CSS directly into the code which YOU SHOULD NOT! Put it
into a separate style sheet):

I made an outer container too, which you don't necessarily need, but
often like to do it.
I made one div for the header, one content div containing first the
picture and the text and then the three text boxes. You might want to
group them within their own divs too.
And then a bottom div.
Hope this helps.

Best regards
Sebastian

If you are totally stuck send me an email and we'll see if we can work
it out.

&lt;div id=&quot;container&quot; style=&quot;width: 100%&quot;&gt;

&lt;div id=&quot;header&quot; style=&quot;width: 100%; display: block;&quot;&gt;
Content for header
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div id=&quot;content&quot;&gt;

&lt;div id=&quot;picture&quot; style=&quot;width: 33%; float: left&quot;&gt;
&lt;img ... /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;some_id&quot; style=&quot;width: 99%; float: left&quot;&gt;
Some content
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&quot;width: 33%; float: left;&quot;&gt;
Box 1
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;width: 33%; float: left;&quot;&gt;
Box 2
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;width: 33%; float: left;&quot;&gt;
Box 3
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div id=&quot;footer&quot; style=&quot;width: 100%; display: block;&quot;&gt;
Content for footer
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

